---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const publishedAt = '2026-04-29';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Costco Hot Dog Calories Without Bun"
  description="A Costco hot dog without the bun contains approximately 370 calories. Full nutrition breakdown for low-carb eaters."
  type="article"
  publishedAt={publishedAt}
>
  <article class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8 py-12">
    <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Calories Without Bun</h1>
    <p class="text-lg text-gray-600 mb-8">For low-carb eaters and calorie counters who skip the bread.</p>

    <div class="bg-yellow-50 border border-yellow-200 rounded-xl p-8 text-center mb-10">
      <p class="text-sm text-yellow-700 font-medium uppercase tracking-wide">Hot Dog Only</p>
      <p class="text-5xl font-bold text-yellow-800 mt-2">370</p>
      <p class="text-yellow-700">calories</p>
    </div>

    <div class="bg-white rounded-xl shadow-sm border border-gray-200 overflow-hidden mb-8">
      <table class="w-full">
        <thead class="bg-gray-50"><tr><th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold">Nutrient</th><th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold">Without Bun</th><th class="px-6 py-3 text-left text-sm font-semibold">With Bun</th></tr></thead>
        <tbody class="divide-y divide-gray-200">
          <tr><td class="px-6 py-3">Calories</td><td class="px-6 py-3 font-medium">370</td><td class="px-6 py-3 text-gray-500">570</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-6 py-3">Total Fat</td><td class="px-6 py-3">29g</td><td class="px-6 py-3 text-gray-500">33g</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-6 py-3">Carbs</td><td class="px-6 py-3 font-medium text-green-700">2g</td><td class="px-6 py-3 text-gray-500">46g</td></tr>
          <tr><td class="px-6 py-3">Protein</td><td class="px-6 py-3">22g</td><td class="px-6 py-3 text-gray-500">24g</td></tr>
        </tbody>
      </table>
    </div>

    <p class="text-gray-700">Skipping the bun removes about 200 calories and 44g of carbohydrates, making the hot dog compatible with low-carb and keto diets. The bun contributes most of the carbs, while the hot dog itself is primarily protein and fat.</p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
